Try (D) and follow the same steps. Label angleBas 40° and angleZas 63°. AngleCis again 63°. Solve for angleY: 77° +Y° + 63° = 180°, 140° +Y° = 180°, andY° = 40°. Label the triangles with this information to see that the triangles now have the same three angle measures. The answer is (D).close
